Organizations should implement the following security measures when using Software Certificates as part of Multi-Factor Authentication:
• Harden the devices being used as much as possible, such as implementing the Essential Eight from the Strategies to Mitigate Cyber Security Incidents (if applicable);
• Ensuring users receive a visual notification each time an authentication request is generated that requires them to enter their PIN or password to access their software certificate;
• Storing the software certificate in the device's TPM (if present), otherwise storing it in the device's certificate store rather than in a regular file on the device's local storage;
• Instructing users to report the theft or loss of their device, even if it is a personal device, as soon as practical.
